[The above information, as compiled by the Romanian authorities, is useful though not complete (e.g. Armenia). Croatia borders the LSD-infected countries Serbia and Montenegro. In difference with Croatia, Romania has maintained, thus far, its non-vaccination policy in relation to LSD. This decision is probably based upon risk-assessment study, in which Romania's status as a major exporter of livestock and their products, including live cattle, has been a considerable factor (see 20160623.4305647).

Bosnia and Herzegovina's epidemiological situation is similar to Croatia's: it neighbours infected Serbia and Montenegro. It will be interesting to note if preventive vaccination is being considered there. - Mod.AS]
